sed as scientific knowledge.\n\n- Eraldo\n|\nGet a grip on yourself. there's only one god here on earth, and that's you. If you don't like the world, make one you like better.\n\n- Yasmina\n|\nLove is a trap. When it appears, we see only its light, not its shadows.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, By the River Piedra I Sat Down and Wept\n|\nEven one day lost in misery is a great loss, for the day will never come back again. You lose 24 hours of happiness, joy & bliss. Live each day in happiness.\n\n- RVM\n|\nWhen you don't know a thing, learn. When you know the truth, teach.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA pear should come to the table popped with juice,Ripened in warmth and served in warmth. On termsLike these, autumn beguiles the fatalist.\n\n- Wallace Stevens, The Palm at the End of the Mind: Selected Poems and a Play\n|\nDon’t follow someone else’s map. You should glean teachings from all directions, keeping true to those that bring progress yet remaining open to changes in yourself.\n\n- Deepak Chopra, The Book of Secrets: Unlocking the Hidden Dimensions of Your Life\n|\nMichael had once read to her how God had cast a man and woman out of paradise. Yet, for all their human faults and failures. God had shown them the way back in.\n\n- Francine Rivers, Redeeming Love\n|\nWhen you lose your job, you gain ownership of your life\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIt is hard to think differently. To change your world, change your thoughts.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nHe realized he needed strength, sustenance that couldn’t come from bread alone. He desperately needed God.\n\n- J.E.B. Spredemann, An Unforgivable Secret\n|\nI'm generally a happy person -with the help of antidepressants, that is- so there is something to be said for surrounding myself with happy people.\n\n- Rachel Machacek, The Science of Single: One Woman's Grand Experiment in Modern Dating, Creating Chemistry, and Finding Love\n|\nMost of the very few people who would choose a good heart over riches would eventually use that to either make a lot of money, or attract men or women who are rich.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nLet others scream, because ultimately you know your story\n\n- Prateek\n|\nYour beauty is tragic.It is the sweetest sin,Heaven ever created!\n\n- Shillpi\n|\nThe life and passion of a person leave an imprint on the ether of a place. Love does not remain within the heart, it flows out to build secret tabernacles in a landscape.\n\n- John O'Donohue, Anam Cara: A Book of Celtic Wisdom\n|\nThe Destiny of Man is to unite, not to divide. If you keep on dividing you end up as a collection of monkeys throwing nuts at each other out of separate trees.\n\n- T.H. White, The Once and Future King\n|\nAbout all you can do in life is be who you are. Some people will love you for you. Most will love you for what you can do for them, and some won't like you at all.\n\n- Rita\n|\nWhen someone is stalking you because they think you are stalking them, it makes you wonder who really is the true stalker?\n\n- Shannon\n|\nYou are a hole in my life, a black hole. Anything I place there cannot be returned. I miss you terribly. Ci vedremo lassu, angelo.\n\n- Timothy Conigrave, Holding the Man\n|\nMany things the gods achieve beyond our judgement,'' said the sorrowful girl. ''What we thought is not confirmed and what we thought not God contives.\n\n- John Irving, A Prayer for Owen Meany\n|\nPlus on évolue dans sa vie, plus on se débarrasse des croyances quinous limitent, et plus on a de choix. Et le choix, c'est la liberté.\n\n- Laurent Gounelle, L'homme qui voulait être heureux\n|\nGod arranges everything for us, so that we need have no more fear or trouble and may be quite sure that all things will come right in the end.\n\n- Johanna Spyri, Heidi\n|\nThere will be haters, there will be doubters, there will be non-believers, and then there will be you proving them wrong.\n\n- Jennifer Van Allen, The Runner's World Big Book of Running for Beginners: Lose Weight, Get Fit, and Have Fun!\n|\nYou see, from where I stand, there are a couple of ways. You continue your journey and you will find your path or the path is already there and you aren't just able to see it.\n\n- Ackshat Deoli, Kilol-Bruges Express: The Fading Nomad\n|\nFill your mind Holy Scripture, that speak life into your life.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nFriendships - and indeed most relationships - are measured in the closeness of hearts, minds and soul ties... not in the distance of physical miles or even the passing of time.\n\n- Rasheed\n|\nIt is clear that the individual who persecutes a man, his brother, because he is not of the same opinion, is a monster.\n\n- Voltaire\n|\nRemember, how you live your Life is far more important than how much you earn. Life soon ends. What matters is whether you enjoyed Life and Lived meaningfully.\n\n- RVM\n|\nHonestly, I don’t know what I would recommend from this story. Perhaps it is this: if you have the choice to laugh or do nothing, you might as well laugh.\n\n- F.K. Preston, The Artist, The Audience and a Man Called Nothing\n|\nI set out to discover the why of it, and to transform my pleasure into knowledge.\n\n- Charles\n|\nI contemplated man's little spark, what it should be valued before God alongside of this great work of heaven and earth.\n\n- Jakob Böhme, The Signature of All Things 1622: As Above So Below\n|\nSometimes it's easier to go on living, not even knowing who you are, when at least you know precisely where you are while you go on not knowing.\n\n- Fredrik Backman, Britt-Marie Was Here\n|\nUntil the day when God shall deign to reveal the future to man, all human wisdom is summed up in these two words,-Wait and hope.\n\n- Alexandre Dumas, The Count of Monte Cristo\n|\nI’m alive,” he groaned. “But I’m not doing a very good job of it.\n\n- Merrie Haskell, The Castle Behind Thorns\n|\nInstead of committing suicide, people go to work.\n\n- Thomas Bernhard, Correction\n|\nPeople expected something for nothing, that’s why they did nothing so beautifully these days.\n\n- Holly Hood, Prison of Paradise\n|\nThey knew, though, she would not suffer as they had suffered. She was perfect. They were scarred.\n\n- Francesca Lia Block, The Rose and the Beast: Fairy Tales Retold\n|\nThe more you understand your true spiritual identity, and your connection with the Supreme, the easier it will be to love your Self.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nI've come to believe that in everyone's life, there's one undeniable moment of change, a set of circumstances that suddenly alters everything.\n\n- Nicholas Sparks, Safe Haven\n|\nNo one is born with fear: we learn it, create it, and perpetuate it. Therefore, fear's biggest secret is we also control it.\n\n- Ken\n|\nEvery life has a destiny... the trick is to discover it before then end of your life. Otherwise, you will have too many regrets.\n\n- Kevin J. Anderson, A Forest of Stars\n|\nWhen you look into the mirror, you can’t even see your heart; but when God looks at your shadow, He sees your soul.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWhat one generation finds ridiculous, the next accepts; and the third shudders when it looks back on what the first did.\n\n- Peter\n|\n...At the end of the day, what matters is our faith in humanity...\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, The Union Moujik\n|\nEven as your body betrays you, your mind denies it.\n\n- Sara Gruen, Water for Elephants\n|\nThe wise man who has become accustomed to necessities knows better how to share with others than how to take from them, so great a treasure of self-sufficiency has he found.\n\n- Epicurus, Epicurus: Letters, Principal Doctrines, and Vatican Sayings"